				<p><p>I played quite a lot with the lego mindstorms and indeed they are interesting but I found them quite limited at the ARM level. The other point with them is that when you move to another Core like the raspberry which I find more interesting (but I am a developper) is that you can continue using the lego parts with it.<br>
So depending where you want to focus on, lego is a good start for all the bricks, sensors and motors but if it is for more programming raspberry will be a good choice.<br><br>
Tosbiak gave some link on the lego so I will just complete with a link on raspberry: <a href="https://www.raspberrypi.org/resources/" rel="nofollow">https://www.raspberrypi.org/resources/</a> (for exemple the butler is quite and interesting robot to make)</p>
